      • openForReading

        default java.io.InputStream openForReading​(ProgressReporter reporter)
        Opens something that can be read, returning an input stream. The given progress reporter is called for each byte that is read from the input stream. If the input size is known (meaning that bytes() returns a non-null value), the reporter will be initialized with the number of bytes to allow percent completion to be computed as the stream is read.
        Parameters:
        reporter - A progress reporter that is called for each byte that is read
        Returns:
        The input stream to read from
